every type of player has a differant special ability, and he may use it improve his situation at the cost of resources
player type 1 - Warrior:
special ability: Avenger's sheild - randomly hits one enemy within range < 3 for 10% of the warrior’s max health, and heals the warrior by (10 × defense: capped at health pool). this ability has a cooldown, meaning it can only be used once for every "ability game tick", and he can't cast it if the remaining cooldown > 0
properties: 
ability cooldown: Integer )gets it in the constructor, repsents the number of game ticks that must pass between each time he can cast his ability)
remaining cooldown: Integer (initialized at 0, represents the number of ticks left until he can cast his ability again)
-upon leveling up (in addition to the normal updates of all player types):
remaining cooldown = 0
health pool = health pool + (5 * level)
attack = attack + (2 * level)
defense = defense + (1 * level)

on each game tick: remaining cooldown = remaining cooldown - 1
on ability cast:
remaining cooldown = ability cooldown
current health = min (healthPool, current health + (10 * defense)
